cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about visual tracking using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for filter generation using RNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses matrix multiplications and convolution operations, which are common in neural networks and signal processing, respectively, and could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
